== Roasted Vegetables ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce} lengthwise. Halve, peel, and cut @red onion{1}(cut into ½-inch-thick wedges); mince a few wedges until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Toss Brussels sprouts and onion wedges on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%teaspoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Mashed Potatoes ==

While veggies roast, dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces.

> For a smoother texture, peel potatoes first.

Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot. Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

== Bavette Steak & Pan Sauce ==

While potatoes cook, pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer steak to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

Meanwhile, strip @rosemary{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until you have 2 tsp (3 tsp for 4 servings).

> Swap in chicken or steak for pork. Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook steak
> to desired doneness, 5-7 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for steak over medium heat. Add minced onion and chopped rosemary. Cook, stirring often, until onion is softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @chicken stock concentrate{1} and ¼ cup water (1⁄3 cup for 4 servings). Bring to a simmer and cook until slightly thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) until melted.

== Finish & Serve ==

Return pot with drained potatoes to medium-low heat. Add @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season generously with salt and pepper.

Slice steak crosswise.

Divide steak, mashed potatoes, and veggies between plates. Top steak with sauce and serve.

> Thinly slice chicken or steak against the grain.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.